    "id": "cmgcir3m30011xmlh5ojpqpax",
    "title": "Music Producer / Recording Engineer",
    "description": "Openings: 1\nLocation: Nairobi ‚Äì Mathare North (Thika Rd service / Kwa Chief loop)\n\n\nOverview:\nMaking hits isn‚Äôt magic it‚Äôs precision, vision, and collaboration. As a Producer/Engineer, you‚Äôll take songs from rough ideas to polished tracks ready for radio and social feeds. You‚Äôll guide artists through songwriting, arrangements, tracking, and mixing, while keeping session files tidy and studio time running like clockwork. Deadlines are tight, but so is the need for creative freedom and sonic quality.\n\nOur client wants someone who thrives both behind the console and in the room with artists. You‚Äôll make technical choices that shape the emotional impact of a track, whether it‚Äôs a vocal comp, an instrument layering, or a synth tweak. Every EQ, plugin, and gain stage matters; every track has to be ready for streaming, mastering, and public ears without compromise.\n\nStudio management is part of the craft. From session backups to plugin updates, patching out problems before they happen, you‚Äôre the person who keeps the gears moving while artists focus on performance. File hygiene is as important as vibe loose tracks or missing stems can undo hours of work.\n\nCollaboration is continuous. You‚Äôll liaise with A&R, communicate timelines, and incorporate feedback, balancing artist creativity with commercial deadlines. The work is fast, dynamic, and sometimes high-pressure, but every polished release is a testament to your technical skill and musical intuition. Success here is measured in smooth sessions, satisfied artists, and tracks that hit their mark. Your growth path leads to Senior Producer, then Studio Manager, and eventually Head of Production at a label putting you at the center of Nairobi‚Äôs music scene and shaping the sound of the city‚Äôs next hits.\n\n\nKey Responsibilities:\n- Pre-production; arrangement; sound design; session planning.\n- Track vocals/instruments; comp and tune responsibly.\n- Mix for platforms; prep for mastering; manage stems.\n- Maintain session backups; manage plugin updates.\n- Liaise with A&R for feedback and release timelines.\n\nEducation & Experience:\n- Audio/Music Tech diplomas + 3‚Äì5 yrs in a commercial studio.\n\nSkills & Tools:\n- DAWs (Pro Tools/Logic/Ableton), mics/preamps, tuning, gain staging.\n\nKPIs:\n- Release acceptance, turnaround time, session uptime, artist satisfaction.\n\nCompensation (Kenya):\nKES 120,000‚Äì185,000 + per-project fees & points (where applicable).\nEstimates; actuals vary with DAW mastery, genre versatility, label budgets, and whether points/royalties are negotiated. Some engagements are retainer + per-track.\n\nBenefits:\n- Medical, studio gear budget, trainings, industry events.\n\nGrowth Path:\n- Senior Producer ‚Üí Studio Manager ‚Üí Head of Production (Label).\nIdeal promotion cycle.",
