    "description": "Openings: 1\nLocation: Nairobi ‚Äì Muthaiga (Kiambu Rd / Forest edge)\n\n\nOverview:\nEditing is where stories truly come alive, and here you won‚Äôt just cut footage, you‚Äôll sculpt narratives that stick. From immersive documentaries to branded films and mini-series, every frame is a chance to captivate, inform, or inspire. You‚Äôll be shaping story arcs that hold audiences from the first second to the last, blending pacing, emotion, and visual rhythm with precision.\n\nCollaboration is part of your daily DNA. You‚Äôll work closely with directors, producers, motion designers, and sound artists to translate concepts into cinematic realities. Feedback loops are fast and creative; you‚Äôll learn to absorb notes without losing your own editorial instincts. The best editors know when to follow guidance and when to assert a bolder vision and here, both are valued.\n\nTechnical mastery is expected, but storytelling is king. From color grading that conveys mood to sound polishing that sharpens impact, every detail counts. Managing proxies, backups, and project hygiene is as critical as assembling the perfect cut. A messy timeline is a timeline that kills creativity, so organization and foresight are part of your craft.\n\nLegal and rights considerations aren‚Äôt just paperwork; they‚Äôre part of the professional editor‚Äôs toolkit. Music licensing, footage releases, and proper clearances must be baked into your workflow. Your edits need to be ready for public distribution without a hitch, combining artistry with compliance in seamless balance.\n\nDeadlines here are real, but so is the satisfaction of seeing your work live, whether on festivals, streaming platforms, or branded campaigns. This role is perfect for someone who thrives in the rhythm of production cycles, loves problem-solving in post, and wants to see their vision translated into stories that resonate widely.\n\n\nKey Responsibilities:\n- Assemble rough cuts; refine pacing, structure, and s